    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-04T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-04T04:00:00-05:00" n="213"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00111 Armament Control/984: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-04T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 4, 1936—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 4—9:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>310. Department’s 71, June 20, 1 p.m. Embassy would appreciate any expression of
                    opinion the Department would care to give as to the nature of the reply which
                    should be made to requests now being received from American firms for assistance
                    in connection with trade transactions with Italy entered into subsequent to the
                    Department’s telegram No. 200, November 13, 6 p.m., 1935,<note n="68"
                        xml:id="d213fn68">
                        <ref target="frus1935v01#pg_818">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1935, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 818</ref>.</note> regarding trade
                    promotion activities in Italy and prior to the Department’s telegram 71 of June
                    20th revoking the instruction contained therein.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
